CONTROLS_TYPE_TOOLTIP: Set camera to orbit or fly mode
KEYBOARD_NAVIGATION_DESCRIPTION:
Click and hold to move.
You can also use mouse in conjunction with keys.
MEASUREMENTS_ADD_HORIZONTAL_AREA: Measure rectangular horizontal Area. Click at three points in a horizontal plan.
MEASUREMENTS_ADD_LINE: Measure distance between two points. Click at the start point and the end point.
MEASUREMENTS_ADD_POLYGON: Measure an area of a polygon. Click at least 3 points and end with Esc.
MEASUREMENTS_ADD_POLYLINE: Measure the length of a continuous polyline. Click at any number of points and end with Esc.
MEASUREMENTS_ADD_VERTICAL_AREA: Measure rectangular vertical Area. Click at two points in a vertical plan.
MEASUREMENTS_ADD_VOLUME: Measure volume of a box. Click at three points in a horizontal plan and the fourth to give it height.
MOUSE_NAVIGATION_DESCRIPTION: Click and drag to rotate, and pan the view. Use mouse wheel to zoom the view. Left click to select
TOUCH_NAVIGATION_DESCRIPTION: Use gestures to zoom, pan and select
ADD_SLICE_X: Add vertical slice along Y-axis. Select a point.
ADD_SLICE_Y: Add vertical slice along X-axis. Select a point.
ADD_SLICE_Z: Add horizontal slice. Select a point.
ADD_SLICE_XY: Add vertical slice. Select two points.
ADD_CROP_BOX: Create crop box. Select three points in a horizontal plane, then select a fourth point for height.
CLIP_TOOL: Create, edit crop boxes, and slice planes
CLIP_APPLY: Apply selected crop box to a model. Otherwise, apply to all slice planes
CLIP_SHOW_SELECTED_ONLY: Show/hide slicing planes and crop boxes that are not selected
CLIP_SHOW_ON_TOP: Show crop boxes and slices on top
CLIP_NEXT: Set next crop box or slicing plane as global clipping
CLIP_PREV: Set previous crop box or slicing plane as global clipping
